      {
        "id": "mineru_exam_paper_en-file-putnam-archive_2003_Solutions_2003s_page_001_5",
        "observed_type": "text",
        "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
        "text": "A2 First solution: Assume without loss of generality that aj + bi > 0 for each i (otherwise both sides of the desired inequality are zero). Then the AM-GM inequality gives and likewise with the roles of a and b reversed. Adding these two inequalities and clearing denominators yields the desired result.",
        "bbox": [
          0.10196078431372549,
          0.48727272727272725,
          0.49098039215686273,
          0.5321212121212121
        ],
        "order": 10
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "eu_id": "EU-0003",
    "kind": "text_cluster_panel",
    "page": "exam_paper_en-file-putnam-archive_2003_Solutions_2003s_page_001",
    "primary_id": "mineru_exam_paper_en-file-putnam-archive_2003_Solutions_2003s_page_001_14",
    "source": "text_cluster",
    "member_count": 2,
    "elements": [
      {
        "id": "mineru_exam_paper_en-file-putnam-archive_2003_Solutions_2003s_page_001_14",
        "observed_type": "text",
        "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
        "text": "is an increasing function of x, so f \"(x) > 0 and Jensen's inequality thus yields the desired result. (As long as the ai are all positive, equality holds when s1 = … . = s, i.e., when the vectors (a1, . . . , an) and (b1, . . . , bn). Of course other equality cases crop up if some of the ai vanish, i.e., if a1 = b1 = 0.)",
        "bbox": [
          0.556078431372549,
          0.5121212121212121,
          0.92,
          0.6
        ],
        "order": 11
      },
      {
        "id": "mineru_exam_paper_en-file-putnam-archive_2003_Solutions_2003s_page_001_15",
        "observed_type": "text",
        "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
        "text": "Fourth solution: We apply induction on n, the case n = 1 being evident. First we verify the auxiliary inequality for a, b, c,d ≥ 0. The left side can be written as",
        "bbox": [
          0.5576470588235294,
          0.6048484848484849,
          0.9192156862745098,
          0.6345454545454545
        ],
        "order": 12
      }
    ]
