        "id": "mineru_exam_paper_en-file-putnam-archive_2003_Solutions_2003s_page_001_7",
        "observed_type": "text",
        "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
        "text": "Second solution: Write the desired inequality in the form",
        "bbox": [
          0.12627450980392158,
          0.6763636363636364,
          0.49019607843137253,
          0.7048484848484848
        ],
        "order": 15
      },
      {
        "id": "mineru_exam_paper_en-file-putnam-archive_2003_Solutions_2003s_page_001_8",
        "observed_type": "text",
        "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
        "text": "expand both sides, and compare the terms on both sides in which k of the terms are among the aj. On the left, one has the product of each k-element subset of {1, . . , n}; on the right, one has",
        "bbox": [
          0.12549019607843137,
          0.7448484848484849,
          0.49098039215686273,
          0.8036363636363636
        ],
        "order": 16
      }
    ]
